snippet: Leading from start to finish, Simone Biles of the United States became the first woman in 11 years to win consecutive all-around gold medals at the gymnastics world championships on Friday in Nanning, China.
lead_paragraph: Leading from start to finish, Simone Biles of the United States became the first woman in 11 years to win consecutive all-around gold medals at the gymnastics world championships on Friday in Nanning, China.

headline.main: American Claims Second Straight All-Around Gold
headline.print_headline: American Claims Second Straight All-Around Gold
